// Config.xcconfig — committed base config.
//
// This file is the entry point that xcodegen wires into both Debug and
// Release. It deliberately defines nothing of its own; its only job is
// to optionally pull in your per-developer settings.
//
// Each developer (and CI runner) creates Config.local.xcconfig from the
// committed Config.local.xcconfig.example and sets DEVELOPMENT_TEAM to
// their own Apple Developer team ID. See docs/SIGNING.md.
//
// The "#include?" form is the optional include: if the local file is
// missing (e.g. a fresh clone), xcodebuild simply continues without it,
// which is what we want — Debug builds use ad-hoc signing ("-") and
// only Release archives need a real team. For local companion runs that
// need Full Disk Access to persist across rebuilds, run:
//   make setup-companion-signing
//   make run-companion
// If macOS is stuck on an old dev app row, run:
//   make reset-companion-fda

#include? "Config.local.xcconfig"
